1
00:01:31,380 --> 00:01:34,830
[Silent Tides]

2
00:01:35,289 --> 00:01:37,970
[Episode 27]

3
00:01:38,070 --> 00:01:39,500
And the smuggling target

4
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:41,310
is Lin Nianci,
Magistrate of Zhongshan County.

5
00:01:41,310 --> 00:01:43,940
[No smoking or fire in the warehouse]

6
00:01:43,940 --> 00:01:44,900
It's fake.

7
00:01:46,310 --> 00:01:49,509
Complete nonsense.

8
00:01:49,830 --> 00:01:52,130
Wang Qizheng works
for the Nanjing government.

9
00:01:52,130 --> 00:01:53,990
Why would he avoid a declaration?

10
00:01:58,130 --> 00:01:58,970
[No smoking or fire in the warehouse]

11
00:01:58,970 --> 00:02:00,940
You and He Xian

12
00:02:01,300 --> 00:02:02,710
are conspiring together,

13
00:02:02,710 --> 00:02:03,780
framing others

14
00:02:03,780 --> 00:02:05,510
and making false accusations.

15
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:08,160
Colonel Sawa, that's going too far.

16
00:02:08,180 --> 00:02:09,250
Too far?

17
00:02:09,270 --> 00:02:09,690
Those corrupt officials
of the Nanjing government

18
00:02:09,690 --> 00:02:11,150
[No smoking or fire in the warehouse]

19
00:02:11,150 --> 00:02:13,410
smuggling behind your Japanese backs

20
00:02:13,410 --> 00:02:15,940
to line their own pockets—
isn't that common?

21
00:02:19,250 --> 00:02:20,650
Even if Colonel Sawa doesn't believe it,

22
00:02:20,650 --> 00:02:23,140
Wang Qizheng's signature can't be fake.

23
00:02:23,170 --> 00:02:23,860
If you want,

24
00:02:23,860 --> 00:02:23,900
[No smoking or fire in the warehouse]

25
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:26,210
you can verify the handwriting.

26
00:02:28,930 --> 00:02:32,450
You've really set up a good trap.

27
00:02:33,650 --> 00:02:35,030
But don't forget,

28
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:36,640
Lin Nianci

29
00:02:37,060 --> 00:02:38,190
will soon bring

30
00:02:38,190 --> 00:02:40,520
the prisoners and confessions
from Zhongshan.

31
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:42,940
No matter what tricks you and He Xian try,

32
00:02:42,970 --> 00:02:44,500
once the witnesses arrive,

33
00:02:45,780 --> 00:02:47,450
your scheme will fall apart.

34
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:49,600
[No smoking or fire in the warehouse]

35
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:50,410
Chief,

36
00:02:50,810 --> 00:02:51,670
I have a report.

37
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:52,900
What is it? Speak!

38
00:02:57,110 --> 00:02:59,850
Something happened in Zhongshan.

39
00:03:07,410 --> 00:03:09,560
After a joint investigation
by Portuguese and Japanese authorities,

40
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:11,220
the Steamship Sai On incident

41
00:03:11,290 --> 00:03:14,070
was solely caused by Lin Nianci,
an official of the Nanjing government,

42
00:03:14,070 --> 00:03:17,200
colluding with Wang Qizheng,
a corrupt Macau merchant, for smuggling.

43
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:19,940
The Japanese case officer, Sawa Eisaku,

44
00:03:19,970 --> 00:03:21,150
at the time of the incident,

45
00:03:21,150 --> 00:03:22,530
used force without authorization,

46
00:03:22,530 --> 00:03:25,660
injuring many Macau police officers
and civilians.

47
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:27,860
During the investigation,
without verification,

48
00:03:27,860 --> 00:03:29,280
he deliberately distorted facts,

49
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,480
provoked incidents,

50
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:34,010
and even attempted to force
a prominent Macau businessman,

51
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:35,900
Mr. He Xian, to give false testimony,

52
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:38,079
falsely accusing the Macau government
of violating neutrality

53
00:03:38,079 --> 00:03:39,660
and participating in smuggling.

54
00:03:39,660 --> 00:03:40,640
In conclusion,

55
00:03:40,870 --> 00:03:43,260
we hereby issue a formal note

56
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:45,240
to the Japanese government

57
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,640
and the Southern China
Expeditionary Army Command

58
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:47,670
making the following demands.

59
00:03:47,670 --> 00:03:48,370
First,

60
00:03:48,390 --> 00:03:50,070
the immediate return of Steamship Sai On.

61
00:03:50,070 --> 00:03:50,670
Second,

62
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:53,930
reasonable compensation
for the injured Macau police

63
00:03:53,950 --> 00:03:55,300
and civilians at the pier.

64
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:55,860
Third,

65
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:58,460
termination of the Portuguese-Japanese
joint anti-smuggling agreement

66
00:03:58,460 --> 00:04:01,430
and cancellation of Japan's armed
anti-smuggling rights in Macau.

67
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:01,980
Fourth,

68
00:04:02,190 --> 00:04:03,490
a formal apology

69
00:04:03,510 --> 00:04:06,300
to the Macau government

70
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:07,650
and the falsely accused
innocent businessman, Mr. He Xian,

71
00:04:07,650 --> 00:04:11,310
with a guarantee that similar incidents
will never happen again.

72
00:04:18,930 --> 00:04:21,370
Our Command has confirmed

73
00:04:21,779 --> 00:04:24,070
that the entire Steamship Sai On incident

74
00:04:24,070 --> 00:04:26,150
was completely a misunderstanding.

75
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:27,670
The Command accepts

76
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:31,010
all demands made by your government.

77
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:31,990
Now,

78
00:04:32,430 --> 00:04:34,560
on behalf of the Japanese government,

79
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:36,690
I extend sincere apologies

80
00:04:37,010 --> 00:04:37,600
to the Macau government

81
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:38,600
and

82
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:41,200
Mr. He Xian.

83
00:04:41,690 --> 00:04:44,810
We hope your government
will not harbor any grudges

84
00:04:45,260 --> 00:04:50,210
and continue to maintain
Japan-Portugal friendly cooperation.

85
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:03,970
You.

86
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:11,960
Colonel Sawa.

87
00:05:21,620 --> 00:05:23,350
Your Excellency the Governor,

88
00:05:24,590 --> 00:05:25,560
I'm sorry.

89
00:05:27,310 --> 00:05:29,200
Please accept my apology.

90
00:05:34,070 --> 00:05:34,870
Colonel Sawa,

91
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:37,400
those you need to apologize to

92
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:39,800
aren't just the Macau government.

93
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:11,960
I'm sorry,

94
00:06:14,780 --> 00:06:15,680
Mr. He.

95
00:06:23,410 --> 00:06:25,290
Please forgive me.

96
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:45,130
[Kiang Wu Hospital Operating Room Launch]

97
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:53,950
[Kiang Wu Hospital Operating Room Launch]

98
00:06:53,950 --> 00:06:54,420
All right.

99
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:55,450
Everyone, smile.

100
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,270
Smile. Good.

101
00:06:58,270 --> 00:06:59,310
Ready.

102
00:06:59,310 --> 00:07:00,220
One.

103
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:01,190
Two.

104
00:07:01,940 --> 00:07:04,330
[Kiang Wu Hospital Operating Room Launch]

105
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:05,600
Commander Ou!

106
00:07:05,620 --> 00:07:06,600
Comrade Yu.

107
00:07:06,620 --> 00:07:07,420
Commander Ou.

108
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:09,610
Thank you for your hard work.

109
00:07:09,610 --> 00:07:10,870
It's our duty.

110
00:07:11,370 --> 00:07:13,240
These supplies are exactly
what we urgently need.

111
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:14,870
We'll make good use of them.

112
00:07:15,450 --> 00:07:16,220
Thank you.

113
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:16,600
Thank you.

114
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,630
You're too kind, Commander Ou.

115
00:07:17,630 --> 00:07:18,180
Please.

116
00:07:18,630 --> 00:07:20,290
Welcome, everyone, welcome.

117
00:07:31,810 --> 00:07:32,570
Hold it carefully.

118
00:07:32,570 --> 00:07:33,310
This way.

119
00:07:50,570 --> 00:07:51,100
Let's go.

120
00:08:26,410 --> 00:08:27,380
Haishan.

121
00:08:28,180 --> 00:08:29,180
-Commander!
-Yu.

122
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:30,540
Commander!

123
00:08:30,540 --> 00:08:31,920
Disinfect with alcohol first.

124
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:34,460
Commander, Haishan is awake!

125
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,000
Haishan!

126
00:08:38,990 --> 00:08:39,900
You're awake.

127
00:08:42,580 --> 00:08:43,780
What's going on here?

128
00:08:44,770 --> 00:08:45,270
Well.

129
00:08:45,770 --> 00:08:47,080
I have good news for you.

130
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:48,610
We just won a major victory.

131
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:49,790
All these things

132
00:08:49,790 --> 00:08:51,390
are excellent equipment we've captured.

133
00:08:51,390 --> 00:08:54,010
We've crushed
all 4 enemy encirclement campaigns.

134
00:08:54,010 --> 00:08:56,000
-Yes, we've defeated them all.
-Yes, we've defeated them all.

135
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,350
The enemy has been driven out
of Black Hill!

136
00:08:58,350 --> 00:08:59,750
Right, they're all gone!

137
00:09:05,610 --> 00:09:08,130
Headquarters just

138
00:09:09,050 --> 00:09:11,000
sent transfer orders.

139
00:09:13,780 --> 00:09:15,560
I've been promoted.

140
00:09:15,580 --> 00:09:17,640
I'm to leave for Nanjing immediately

141
00:09:18,390 --> 00:09:21,990
to serve as Chief Advisor
to the Wang administration.

142
00:09:22,990 --> 00:09:25,320
Chief Advisor to the Nanjing government?

143
00:09:25,820 --> 00:09:27,960
Assigning such a nominal position

144
00:09:27,980 --> 00:09:31,180
is a promotion in name
but a demotion in reality, isn't it?

145
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,550
Perhaps.

146
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:37,520
Who can blame them
when this encirclement campaign

147
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:39,450
was a complete failure?

148
00:09:39,780 --> 00:09:41,350
Over these past few years,

149
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:45,670
our work in Macau has made no progress

150
00:09:45,690 --> 00:09:47,840
and suffered setback after setback.

151
00:09:49,090 --> 00:09:52,370
The fact that they still arranged
a Chief Advisor for me

152
00:09:52,850 --> 00:09:55,460
means they're cutting me some slack.

153
00:09:55,910 --> 00:09:56,740
General,

154
00:09:58,030 --> 00:09:59,270
I'm sorry.

155
00:10:00,170 --> 00:10:02,150
I was too careless this time,

156
00:10:02,930 --> 00:10:05,720
which led to the failure
of the Steamship Sai On operation.

157
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:08,170
Command has already reached a conclusion.

158
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:11,020
Regarding the Steamship Sai On case,

159
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:12,360
this time, you

160
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:14,960
successfully seized
a large amount of tungsten ore

161
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:18,410
the Empire of Japan urgently needs,

162
00:10:18,770 --> 00:10:22,360
as well as an entire shipload of diesel.

163
00:10:23,110 --> 00:10:27,040
Even without a complete victory,
your achievements can't be ignored.

164
00:10:27,970 --> 00:10:33,040
This time,
I'll take responsibility for the failure

165
00:10:33,430 --> 00:10:37,180
to give you a chance
to turn things around in Macau.

166
00:10:43,630 --> 00:10:46,730
General Matsui will be replacing me.

167
00:10:48,530 --> 00:10:49,340
Sawa.

168
00:10:50,420 --> 00:10:52,080
I know that over the past year,

169
00:10:52,460 --> 00:10:58,830
you've been pushing for the Imperial Army
to directly occupy Macau.

170
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:04,200
But General Matsui
firmly opposes this strategy.

171
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:05,980
Despite your reluctance,

172
00:11:05,980 --> 00:11:09,120
you'll have to find another way.

173
00:11:10,130 --> 00:11:12,990
As for whether you
can make up for my disappointment

174
00:11:13,370 --> 00:11:14,700
and completely resolve

175
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:18,760
the Macau issue for the Empire,

176
00:11:21,060 --> 00:11:22,420
that's up to you now.

177
00:11:26,270 --> 00:11:27,070
General,

178
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:29,470
I assure you

179
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:32,630
that I will spare no effort

180
00:11:32,630 --> 00:11:34,100
to thoroughly eradicate

181
00:11:34,980 --> 00:11:36,910
the anti-Japanese forces in Macau

182
00:11:38,260 --> 00:11:40,310
at all costs.

183
00:11:47,070 --> 00:11:48,340
I asked you here this time

184
00:11:48,340 --> 00:11:49,930
to repay a favor.

185
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:52,360
A favor? What do you mean?

186
00:11:52,770 --> 00:11:55,100
Last time I asked you to put on an act
in front of Wang Qizheng,

187
00:11:55,100 --> 00:11:56,370
didn't I promise you

188
00:11:56,390 --> 00:11:58,190
that I'd help you make a fortune?

189
00:11:58,540 --> 00:11:59,900
It was nothing.

190
00:11:59,930 --> 00:12:02,060
Xian, you're taking it too seriously.

191
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,650
Is your President Saito from Lyun Coeng

192
00:12:03,650 --> 00:12:05,320
going crazy lately,

193
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:07,030
buying up supplies everywhere?

194
00:12:07,030 --> 00:12:08,680
He wants everything, no matter what it is.

195
00:12:08,680 --> 00:12:10,980
That's true. These Japanese

196
00:12:11,180 --> 00:12:12,290
have gone desperate.

197
00:12:12,290 --> 00:12:13,510
I heard that in their country,

198
00:12:13,510 --> 00:12:15,480
even cooking pots from ordinary homes

199
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:17,180
and nails from the roof beams
have all been collected.

200
00:12:17,180 --> 00:12:19,380
So now, no matter what can be purchased,

201
00:12:19,380 --> 00:12:21,030
Saito is willing to pay top dollar.

202
00:12:21,030 --> 00:12:22,010
As long as one can get the goods,

203
00:12:22,010 --> 00:12:24,720
the company offers
frighteningly high commissions.

204
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:25,650
That's perfect.

205
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,050
Recently, I've gathered

206
00:12:27,050 --> 00:12:29,140
inventory from all merchants across Macau.

207
00:12:29,140 --> 00:12:31,810
There are some machines,
equipment, instruments,

208
00:12:31,810 --> 00:12:33,010
and some small parts.

209
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:35,460
But they're either too old

210
00:12:35,570 --> 00:12:36,790
or incomplete sets.

211
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:39,230
Nobody elsewhere would want them.

212
00:12:39,340 --> 00:12:41,020
But I wonder if President Saito

213
00:12:41,020 --> 00:12:41,890
would mind.

214
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:42,980
Mind? He wouldn't.

215
00:12:42,990 --> 00:12:44,570
Right now, for any metal products

216
00:12:44,570 --> 00:12:45,740
that can be melted down and reused,

217
00:12:45,740 --> 00:12:46,810
he'd be more than happy to take.

218
00:12:46,810 --> 00:12:47,610
Not to mention

219
00:12:47,620 --> 00:12:49,340
there are so many usable items there.

220
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:50,170
But one thing,

221
00:12:50,170 --> 00:12:51,000
Xian,

222
00:12:51,690 --> 00:12:53,900
do you really plan
to sell them to the Japanese?

223
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:55,190
Didn't you just say

224
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:57,360
Saito offers such high commissions?

225
00:12:57,470 --> 00:12:59,000
Once this deal is done,

226
00:12:59,020 --> 00:12:59,650
the fortune I promised you

227
00:12:59,650 --> 00:13:01,840
will be yours.

228
00:13:03,060 --> 00:13:04,100
But, Xian,

229
00:13:05,290 --> 00:13:06,480
are you serious?

230
00:13:06,770 --> 00:13:08,300
You still don't believe me?

231
00:13:10,970 --> 00:13:12,110
However,

232
00:13:13,110 --> 00:13:14,310
I have one condition.

233
00:13:17,070 --> 00:13:17,960
Chairman,

234
00:13:17,980 --> 00:13:21,100
this is the list of supplies
I've recently acquired.

235
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:26,240
Looks like quite a lot.

236
00:13:26,650 --> 00:13:27,590
Well done.

237
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:28,870
Well done.

238
00:13:29,250 --> 00:13:30,530
You're too kind.

239
00:13:30,980 --> 00:13:34,190
Although the quantity is large this time,

240
00:13:34,220 --> 00:13:37,720
the equipment and parts are incomplete,

241
00:13:37,740 --> 00:13:40,610
and they cost a high price.

242
00:13:40,910 --> 00:13:42,840
Why worry about high prices?
Who cares if they're incomplete?

243
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:43,680
These supplies,

244
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:45,750
for factories back home
suffering from bombings,

245
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:47,760
are as precious as gold.

246
00:13:47,780 --> 00:13:48,550
Manager He,

247
00:13:48,860 --> 00:13:50,810
you've done well.

248
00:13:50,930 --> 00:13:52,310
I'm giving you a bonus.

249
00:13:52,330 --> 00:13:53,260
One million.

250
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:54,620
Thank you.

251
00:13:58,050 --> 00:13:59,290
However,

252
00:13:59,740 --> 00:14:02,120
what's urgent now

253
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:05,230
is how to transport these supplies.

254
00:14:05,430 --> 00:14:06,740
As you know,

255
00:14:06,770 --> 00:14:09,890
all the merchant ships in Macau

256
00:14:09,910 --> 00:14:14,430
have been requisitioned by Command.

257
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:18,660
We have no ocean transport capability now.

258
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:26,830
Maybe there's a way
in Guangzhou or Hong Kong?

259
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:27,270
[Lyun Coeng Freight]

260
00:14:27,270 --> 00:14:28,330
I just remembered.

261
00:14:29,020 --> 00:14:30,420
There's an opportunity.

262
00:14:30,850 --> 00:14:32,450
There are supplies
confiscated by Colonel Sawa

263
00:14:32,450 --> 00:14:34,420
in the Steamship Sai On incident.

264
00:14:34,450 --> 00:14:36,790
Headquarters has specifically
arranged a ship

265
00:14:36,790 --> 00:14:38,650
to transport them back home soon.

266
00:14:39,590 --> 00:14:42,060
Our Lyun Coeng shipment isn't that large.

267
00:14:42,270 --> 00:14:45,090
It would only take up a small corner
of the warehouse.

268
00:14:45,090 --> 00:14:45,140
But as you said,

269
00:14:45,140 --> 00:14:47,520
[Lyun Coeng Freight]

270
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:50,950
they're shipping important supplies,
and ours...

271
00:14:51,290 --> 00:14:53,670
They are both crucial supplies
desperately needed back home.

272
00:14:53,670 --> 00:14:55,270
They're equally important.

273
00:14:55,890 --> 00:14:58,470
I'll call the Southern China
Expeditionary Army Command immediately

274
00:14:58,470 --> 00:14:59,830
to make the request.

275
00:14:59,850 --> 00:15:02,200
I'm sure they'll agree.

276
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:02,760
[Lyun Coeng Freight]

277
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:03,550
Manager He,

278
00:15:04,220 --> 00:15:05,580
start preparing right away.

279
00:15:05,580 --> 00:15:07,460
You must personally oversee

280
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:09,620
the transfer of these goods
to Hong Kong for shipping.

