00:40:06,460 --> 00:40:07,120
This

707
00:40:07,150 --> 00:40:09,170
is the newly-received ultimatum

708
00:40:09,210 --> 00:40:11,380
from the Empire of Japan
to the Portuguese Government

709
00:40:11,380 --> 00:40:12,840
and the Macau government.

710
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:16,240
It states that the assassination
of Yasumitsu Fukae

711
00:40:16,270 --> 00:40:19,520
is the greatest provocation
against the Empire of Japan.

712
00:40:20,490 --> 00:40:22,150
The Macau government bears

713
00:40:22,190 --> 00:40:23,980
undeniable responsibility for this.

714
00:40:23,980 --> 00:40:24,850
Therefore,

715
00:40:24,880 --> 00:40:26,800
the Japanese
Southern China Expeditionary Army

716
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:30,210
has imposed a punitive blockade on Macau

717
00:40:30,210 --> 00:40:32,960
and reserves the right
to take further military action

718
00:40:32,960 --> 00:40:35,000
until the facts of this case are clarified

719
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:37,840
and the perpetrator is properly punished.

720
00:40:38,130 --> 00:40:39,630
The Japanese side has appointed

721
00:40:39,630 --> 00:40:43,390
Keiichi Imai,
Deputy Consul General of Guangdong,

722
00:40:43,410 --> 00:40:46,010
to urgently take over
as the new consul in Macau

723
00:40:46,010 --> 00:40:46,940
and proceed to Macau,

724
00:40:46,940 --> 00:40:49,630
demanding that upon Consul Imai's arrival,

725
00:40:49,630 --> 00:40:51,780
he takes over all investigative authority
for this case.

726
00:40:51,780 --> 00:40:54,690
The Macau government and police
must fully cooperate

727
00:40:54,690 --> 00:40:57,090
without any interference or obstruction.

728
00:40:57,280 --> 00:41:00,600
Allowing the Japanese
to conduct investigations in Macau?

729
00:41:00,600 --> 00:41:03,770
This is an outright usurpation
of our judicial sovereignty!

730
00:41:03,770 --> 00:41:06,230
Exactly. This is absolutely unacceptable.

731
00:41:06,340 --> 00:41:08,870
How can we possibly let
the Japanese handle the investigations?

732
00:41:08,870 --> 00:41:10,730
The government should immediately
protest to Japan

733
00:41:10,730 --> 00:41:12,950
and demand they respect international law!

734
00:41:12,950 --> 00:41:13,800
Everyone!

735
00:41:14,800 --> 00:41:16,090
Look carefully.

736
00:41:16,360 --> 00:41:18,230
This is Japan's ultimatum

737
00:41:18,230 --> 00:41:20,030
with no room for negotiation.

738
00:41:20,030 --> 00:41:22,320
The Japanese are fully prepared

739
00:41:22,320 --> 00:41:24,650
to deploy troops to Macau at any moment.

740
00:41:24,650 --> 00:41:26,760
Accept it, or declare war.

741
00:41:26,760 --> 00:41:28,860
No other options!

742
00:41:34,940 --> 00:41:37,230
The immediate issue

743
00:41:37,250 --> 00:41:38,970
is that a foreign consul
has died in Macau.

744
00:41:38,970 --> 00:41:40,240
No matter what,

745
00:41:40,260 --> 00:41:42,510
we do bear some responsibility.

746
00:41:42,710 --> 00:41:44,960
The Japanese don't trust
the Macau government,

747
00:41:44,960 --> 00:41:47,430
and we have no choice
but to accept it now.

748
00:41:51,820 --> 00:41:52,670
Your Excellency the Governor,

749
00:41:52,670 --> 00:41:54,260
there's big trouble with the Fukue case.

750
00:41:54,260 --> 00:41:55,590
What has happened?

751
00:41:55,700 --> 00:41:57,270
The police have just found

752
00:41:57,300 --> 00:41:58,730
the abandoned vehicle
involved in the murder on the shore.

753
00:41:58,730 --> 00:42:01,360
Investigation shows
it belongs to Rodrigues' company.

754
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:02,690
My company's car?

755
00:42:03,170 --> 00:42:04,960
Yes. Along with the car,

756
00:42:04,960 --> 00:42:07,280
your secretary Santos' body
was also found.

757
00:42:07,280 --> 00:42:10,390
One of the murder weapons
from the Fukue case was in his hand.

758
00:42:10,390 --> 00:42:11,520
Damn it.

759
00:42:11,880 --> 00:42:13,200
This is a frame-up.

760
00:42:13,510 --> 00:42:15,790
This is clearly a setup!

761
00:42:17,130 --> 00:42:18,360
Your Excellency the Governor,

762
00:42:18,360 --> 00:42:20,690
when will the new Japanese Consul arrive?

763
00:42:21,320 --> 00:42:23,670
Keiichi Imai has left Guangzhou

764
00:42:23,670 --> 00:42:25,800
and will arrive in Macau at 10 tonight.

765
00:42:29,550 --> 00:42:31,340
So in 5 more hours,

766
00:42:31,370 --> 00:42:32,510
the Japanese will take over

767
00:42:32,510 --> 00:42:33,570
the investigation of the Fukue case?

768
00:42:33,570 --> 00:42:34,050
Yes.

769
00:42:34,160 --> 00:42:36,000
I guess their first search target

770
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:37,780
will definitely be my company
and warehouse.

771
00:42:37,780 --> 00:42:39,670
So we must act before then

772
00:42:39,690 --> 00:42:41,210
and quickly move these supplies

773
00:42:41,210 --> 00:42:42,000
into hiding.

774
00:42:43,590 --> 00:42:46,560
But my fleet has just arrived at the port.

775
00:42:46,730 --> 00:42:48,270
Now the entire Macau

776
00:42:48,300 --> 00:42:49,800
has been completely blockaded

777
00:42:49,800 --> 00:42:51,050
by the Japanese.

778
00:42:51,330 --> 00:42:53,300
The fleet can't leave at all now.

779
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:56,050
Besides,
the quantity of goods is so large.

780
00:42:56,230 --> 00:42:57,870
Just unloading them

781
00:42:57,900 --> 00:42:59,450
took 2 whole days.

782
00:43:01,310 --> 00:43:02,760
In such a short time,

783
00:43:03,730 --> 00:43:04,900
how can we possibly transport everything?
